Class ExceptionMappingBinaryFunction<L,R,O>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BinaryFunction<L,R,O>, java.util.function.Function<L,O>, Relatable

    public abstract class ExceptionMappingBinaryFunction<L,R,O>
extends AbstractBinaryFunction<L,R,O>
    A binary function base class that allows subclasses to throw arbitrary exceptions from their evaluation. Any such exception will be mapped to a runtime exception and then re-thrown from evaluate(Object, Object). This method is overridden to be final, subclasses must implement the abstract method evaluateWithException(Object, Object) instead.

    • Method Detail

      • evaluateWithException

        public abstract O evaluateWithException(L rLeftValue,
                                        R rRightValue)
                                 throws java.lang.Exception
        This method must be implemented by subclasses to perform the function evaluation. The method may throw any type of exception to signal an error. The invoking evaluate(Object, Object) method will convert such exceptions into runtime exceptions.
        Parameters:
        rLeftValue - The left input value for the evaluation
        rRightValue - The right input value for the evaluation
        Returns:
        The result of the evaluation
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - If an error occurs
